theory, and then through the paper's geometric lens.

30:17.100 --> 30:23.940
Let's say a standard historian is counting the total number of elites in both societies to

30:23.940 --> 30:25.340
measure their structural mass.

30:25.920 --> 30:31.640
For both Society 1 and Society 3, the total elite index is exactly 15.

30:32.060 --> 30:33.520
15 elites each.

30:33.520 --> 30:33.960
Yes.

30:34.420 --> 30:40.400
To the standard historian or a modern economist looking at top-line volume metrics, these two

30:40.400 --> 30:42.760
societies look completely identical.

30:42.940 --> 30:43.120
Oh.

30:43.340 --> 30:47.760
They appear to have the exact same capacity and the exact same level of stability.

30:47.960 --> 30:49.760
They both have 15 power players.

